tip.text: Look, for 5€ you cannot expect bufala & DOP on your pizza. It is NOT a contender for best pizza in town but it IS remarkable value.
Good honest Italian fare.
This little place appears to have Italians working both front and back of house. So it's probably pretty authentic.
Your gravest error would be passing on the fries here. Don't sleep on them Frytki.

contact.facebookName: Hotel Kyriad Saint Malo Centre Plage  Vue sur Mer

tip.text: Great food, even better service. The bread though!
Best coffee in town. Look at that delicious crema.
If you're lucky you might come across an opera practice in the main hall - amazing.
Interestingly, one part of this park is designed in a French style and the other in an English style. Very cool contrast.
Run by a Sichuanese family, this is reportedly where the Chinese Embassy folks eat. Pretty close to authentic for Tallinn - great hot & sour soup and baozi, decent dumplings.
This place is flying way under the radar - probably due to location. Lovely looking spot with passionate owners and decent British fare. Good selection of beers to.
Great vibe, average drinks, horrible service. Why are the waitresses at a Chicago-themed bar dressed as French maids?
Feels like a spot with real heart in amongst what now feels like Karakoy's hipster machine. Have the breakfast.

formattedAddress: Mumhane Cad. Fransız Geçidi İş Merkezi Karakoy

tip.text: The design of the place is wonderful, especially the suites and the service is good overall. But be mindful if you book a king bed - these guys think two twins pushed together is the same. It isn't.
Trust me, sitting on a bicycle seat while drinking might seem like a good idea but it really isn't.
Seriously guys, these burgers are not messing around. Get the Vivo and cheesy fries. Just do it.

The Bristol sandwich is like a guy who looks small at first but is hugely jacked & will beat you to death with a chair-leg if given the chance. This is NOT your mum's ham sarnie. Resistance is futile.
Go straight to the top floor. Frescoes and mosaics are amazing.

venue.name: Palazzo Massimo Alle Terme - Museo Nazionale Romano

tip.text: After your feelings about Sultanahmet switch from wondrous (the mosques) to suicidal (the hordes), walk across the Galata bridge and come here for an oasis of serenity.
Food is brilliant. Who indeed doesn't like perfectly executed poached eggs with avo, salmon & goat's cheese?
Coffee roast is a little light for me but the food is brilliant. Quality produce, executed perfectly. Keep it simple: pimp your brekkie.
Cosans says this is a piccolo. In that case, I must be Lebron James.
The coffee is pretty bad, the 'bubbles' water doesn't actually have any bubbles & the staff are pretty clueless but the space looks great - just lower your expectations.

formattedAddress: No 27, Floor 2, Ngo Duc Ke Str., District 1 (Dong Khoi Str.)

tip.text: Super confused service. Took about 10 mins to process "double shot flat white". The result is pictured - I won't be coming here again. These guys don't seem to know how to operate an espresso machine.
A quiet beach indeed. The sand is not the whitest but it's nice enough. Watch out for the tiny sand bubbler crabs scurrying around!

tip.text: Lobster sliders & CW Bleu. Do it.
Great looking place. Tiny & tucked away but very good coffee and a friendly vibe.
If you only do one thing in Hyderabad, you must come here. Book over a week in advance. The high tea was average but the venue is truly mind-blowing.
Stall next to the Revenue Office is not great. Food geared to tourists. Avoid.
Room for improvement (like use better ice pls omg) but having sampled a negroni & a whiskey sour,  these might be the best classic cocktails in Bali. Well-trained bartenders & a great space upstairs.

formattedAddress: Jalan Raya Kerobokan No. 135 (Jalan Sunset Road)

tip.text: Bourdain must've been smoking crack when he called these martinis the best outside NYC. But the ribs are indeed excellent. I suggest you have them with a beer or maybe a Bloody Mary.
The service is indifferent bordering on awkward and the food is remarkably flavourless. Zero idea what all the fuss is about, the fish isn't even fresh. Highlight is their awesome statue of Ganesha.
Contender for Seminyak's best coffee. Decent all day brekkie too. Chill vibe.
As "bread" they serve some delightful frozen roti prata with butter. I'm kidding. It's not delightful.
Apparently this is the place for sticky rice.
The coffee is pretty good & the breakfast is edible (despite an obsession with brioche) but they've crammed in way too many covers which makes the place feel like a prison cafeteria on weekends.
Good try but the coffee needs to be roasted darker if it's to cut through the milk. Tastes washed out even as a double ristretto based flat white. Good milk texture though.

Surprisingly quiet after work given central location. And your refurb wishes have been granted.
